snippet.textDisplay:
Everyone: "Why don't you just get a hysterectomy if you're in pain all of the time?"
Me: "Why don't you cut off your balls and penis?" Then we can talk "Why don't you stick a hot torch up your vagina?" Then we can talk.
I would never ever ask someone personal questions about their private parts. So don't ask me about mine. It's pretty simple. I don't understand why this happens to women with endometriosis/PCOS. I would love to sit down with each person and explain that a hysterectomy wouldn't even help. Or that it's my fertility and I'll talk about it if I want to. But I don't have time or emotional energy to do this. I sit at home and cry enough about it. There is no cure. Let's treat it like you would with a "normal" everyday person. If you wouldn't ask them about their private business, literally, then don't ask me. Don't ask Tati.
